div.p:
First, therfore I deny, that the Communion or Lords Table is
either an Altar, or High Altar, that it ought so to be stiled or reputed,
or that any Altars ought to be set up in our Churches;

Which words are some what darke, but they will be plaine,
if we consider both the thing that the Apostle would prove,
& the reason by which he proveth it.



All which considered, this, Injunction gives no warrant at all
for the late removing of our Tables & railing them in Altarwise,
for wich the Coale is so hote & fiery.

